<div class="dedicationbox"><b>Shouldn't Every Blog Be Dedicated to Someone?</b><br /><br />
This blog is dedicated to my parents who taught me that the family meal is a place for reflection, sharing of stories, and for connection. In our family it is a place of safety and certainty and quite frequently of hilarity. The food served by my parents is always made with care, creativity and generosity of spirit. I share their passion for cooking and their belief that the family meal is a critical anchor for all of us.<br /><br /><h1></h1>

So, to both of my parents who celebrate life's ups and downs by laughing and lingering in the kitchen, this blog is for you.
</div><br /><br />
